  "texts": [
    "However, we believe that the presented analysis is still useful as we observe clear \"hot topics\" that resonate with earlier thematic research areas defined by the WHO which are extremely unlikely to have been researched fully since formulating the gap.",
    "Practical and Research ImplicationsThis study's aim is not to generate research topics automatically that, when worked on, guarantee impact or publication.",
    "Instead, we scope the landscape of research gaps outlined in the literature.",
    "This study should therefore be taken as a help to identify and prioritize \"hot\" topics that need addressing.",
    "This study also does not seek to replace individual literature research in a chosen topic, but it can serve as a guide to formulate specific literature search queries in specific areas related to research questions left as future work by prior publications."
